@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<link href="~/css/Privacy.css" rel="stylesheet" />

<header id="header">
    <div class="container position-relative d-flex align-items-center justify-content-between">
        <a href="@Url.Action("Index","Home")" class="logo d-flex align-items-center">
            <img src="~/assets/img/logo2.png" alt="">
            <h1 class="sitename">EvoluBank</h1>
        </a>
    </div>
</header>

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<h2>Introduction</h2>
<p>At EvoluBank, we are committed to protecting the privacy and security of our clients' personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, share, and safeguard your information when you interact with us, whether online, over the phone, or in person.</p>

<h2>Information We Collect</h2>
<p>We may collect personal information, including but not limited to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Name, address, and contact details (phone number, email, etc.)</li>
    <li>Identification documents (e.g., government-issued ID, passport)</li>
    <li>Financial information, including bank account numbers, transaction history, and income details</li>
    <li>Employment details</li>
    <li>Information obtained through cookies and similar tracking technologies when you visit our website or use our app</li>
</ul>

<h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
<p>We use your personal information to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Open, maintain, and service your accounts</li>
    <li>Process transactions and provide banking services</li>
    <li>Communicate with you about products, services, and updates</li>
    <li>Protect against and detect fraud, unauthorized transactions, claims, or other liabilities</li>
    <li>Comply with legal obligations and regulatory requirements</li>
    <li>Conduct analytics to improve our services</li>
</ul>

<h2>Sharing Your Information</h2>
<p>We do not sell or share your personal information with third parties for marketing purposes without your explicit consent. We may share your data with:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Third-party service providers assisting us in offering banking services</li>
    <li>Regulators, law enforcement, or legal advisors, when required by law or for regulatory compliance</li>
    <li>Other parties involved in transactions, such as payment processors</li>
</ul>

<h2>Security Measures</h2>
<p>We implement robust security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, misuse, or disclosure. These measures include encryption, firewalls, secure servers, and employee training. However, no security system is foolproof, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information.</p>

<h2>Your Privacy Choices</h2>
<p>You may have the right to access, update, or delete your personal information in our records, subject to legal and regulatory constraints. You can also opt out of receiving promotional communications by contacting us directly.</p>

<h2>Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
<p>We use cookies and similar tracking technologies on our website to enhance user experience, analyze trends, and provide tailored content. You can control the use of cookies through your browser settings.</p>

<h2>International Data Transfers</h2>
<p>Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your country of residence. We take steps to ensure that any data transfers comply with applicable data protection laws.</p>

<h2>Updates to this Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in legal, regulatory, or operational requirements. Any updates will be communicated to you via email or our website.</p>

<h2>Contact Us</h2>
<p>
    If you have any questions or concerns regarding our Privacy Policy or the handling of your personal data, please contact us at:<br>
    <a href="mailto:customer.support@evolubank.pt">customer.support@evolubank.pt</a>
</p>

